<span class="displaytext"><b>1. defending his amnesty bill, sen. (candidate last) lost his temper and "screamed, 'f*ck you!' at texas sen. john cornyn" (r-tx).</b> "presidential hopeful (candidate full) - who has been dogged for years by questions about his volcanic temper - erupted in an angry, profanity-laced tirade at a fellow (PARTY NAME) senator, sources told the post yesterday. in a heated dispute over immigration-law overhaul, (candidate last) screamed, 'f--- you!' at texas sen. john cornyn, who had been raising concerns about the legislation. 'this is chickens---stuff,' (candidate last) snapped at cornyn, according to several people in the room off the senate floor thursday. 'you've always been against this bill, and you're just trying to derail it.'" (charles hurt, "raising (candidate last)," <em>new york post</em>, 5/19/07) <p><b>2. in 2000, sen. (candidate last) ran an attack ad comparing then-gov. george w. bush to bill (candidate last).</b> sen. (candidate last): "i guess it was bound to happen. governor bush's campaign is getting desperate, with a negative ad about me. the fact is, i'll use the surplus money to fix social security, cut your taxes and pay down the debt. governor bush uses all of the surplus for tax cuts, with not one new penny for social security or the debt. his ad twists the truth like (candidate last). we're all pretty tired of that. as president, i'll be conservative and always tell you the truth. no matter what." ((candidate last) 2000, campaign ad, 2/9/00; <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uhoxkcprdl4">www.youtube.com/watch?v=uhoxkcprdl4</a>) </p><p><b>3. sen. (candidate last) repeatedly called sen. pete domenici (r-nm) an "a**hole", causing a fellow gop senator to say, "i didn't want this guy anywhere near a trigger."</b> "why can't (candidate last) win the votes of his own colleagues? to explain, a (PARTY NAME) senator tells this story: at a gop meeting last fall, (candidate last) erupted out of the blue at the respected budget committee chairman, pete domenici, saying, 'only an a--hole would put together a budget like this.' offended, domenici stood up and gave a dignified, restrained speech about how in all his years in the senate, through many heated debates, no one had ever called him that. another senator might have taken the moment to check his temper. but (candidate last) went on: 'i wouldn't call you an a--hole unless you really were an a--hole.' the (PARTY NAME) senator witnessing the scene had considered supporting (candidate last) for president, but changed his mind. 'i decided,' the senator told newsweek, 'i didn't want this guy anywhere near a trigger.'" (evan thomas, et al., "senator hothead," <em>newsweek</em>, 2/21/00) </p><p><b>4. sen. (candidate last) had a heated exchange with sen. charles grassley (r-ia) and called him a "f*cking jerk."</b> "senators are not used to having their intelligence or integrity challenged by another senator. 'are you calling me stupid?' sen. chuck grassley once inquired during a debate with (candidate last) over the fate of the vietnam mias, according to a source who was present. 'no,' replied (candidate last), 'i'm calling you a f---ing jerk!' (grassley and (candidate last) had no comment.)" (evan thomas, et al., "senator hothead," <em>newsweek</em>, 2/21/00) </p><p><b>5. in 1995, sen. (candidate last) had a "scuffle" with 92-year-old sen. strom thurmond (r-sc) on the senate floor.</b> "in january 1995, (candidate last) was midway through an opening statement at a senate armed services committee hearing when chairman strom thurmond asked, 'is the senator about through?' (candidate last) glared at thurmond, thanked him for his 'courtesy' (translation: buzz off), and continued on. (candidate last) later confronted thurmond on the senate floor. a scuffle ensued, and the two didn't part friends." (harry jaffe, "senator hothead," <em>the washingtonian</em>, 2/97) </p><p><b>6. sen. (candidate last) accused sen. mitch mcconnell (r-ky) of the "most egregious incident" of corruption he had seen in the senate.</b> "it escalated when (candidate last) reiterated the charges oct. 10 in a cross-examination, calling mcconnell's actions the 'most egregious incident' demonstrating the appearance of corruption he has ever seen in his senate career." (amy keller, "attacks escalate in depositions," <em>roll call</em>, 10/21/02) </p><p><b>7. sen. (candidate last) attacked christian leaders and (PARTY NAME)s in a blistering speech during the 2000 campaign.</b> (candidate last): "unfortunately, governor bush is a pat robertson (PARTY NAME) who will lose to al gore. ... the political tactics of division and slander are not our values... they are corrupting influences on religion and politics, and those who practice them in the name of religion or in the name of the (PARTY NAME) party or in the name of america shame our faith, our party and our country. neither party should be defined by pandering to the outer reaches of american politics and the agents of intolerance, whether they be louis farrakhan or al sharpton on the left, or pat robertson or jerry falwell on the right." (sen. (candidate full), remarks, virginia beach, va, 2/28/00) </p><p><b>8. sen. (candidate last) attacked vice president cheney.</b> (candidate last): "the president listened too much to the vice president ... of course, the president bears the ultimate responsibility, but he was very badly served by both the vice president and, most of all, the secretary of defense." (roger simon, "(candidate last) bashes cheney over iraq policy," <em>the politico</em>, 1/24/07) </p><p><b>9. celebrating his first senate election in 1986, sen. (candidate last) screamed at and harassed a young (PARTY NAME) volunteer.</b> "it was election night 1986, and (candidate full) had just been elected to the u.s. senate for the first time. even so, he was not in a good mood. (candidate last) was yelling at the top of his lungs and poking the chest of a young (PARTY NAME) volunteer who had set up a lectern that was too tall for the 5-foot-9 politician to be seen to advantage, according to a witness to the outburst. 'here this poor guy is thinking he has done a good job, and he gets a new butt ripped because (candidate last) didn't look good on television,' jon hinz told a reporter thursday. at the time, hinz was executive director of the arizona (PARTY NAME) party. ... hinz said (candidate last)'s treatment of the young campaign worker in 1986 troubled him for years. 'there were an awful lot of people in the room,' hinz recalled. 'you'd have to stick cotton in your ears not to hear it. he ((candidate last)) was screaming at him, and he was red in the face. it wasn't right, and i was very upset at him.'" (kris mayes and charles kelly, "stories surface on senator's demeanor," <em>the arizona republic</em>, 11/5/99) </p><p><b>10. sen. (candidate last) "publicly abused" senator richard shelby (r-al).</b> "[(candidate last)] noted his propensity for passion but insisted that he doesn't 'insult anybody or fly off the handle or anything like that.' this is, quite simply, hogwash. (candidate last) often insults people and flies off the handle... there have been the many times (candidate last) has called reporters 'liars' and 'idiots' when they have had the audacity to ask him unpleasant, but pertinent, questions. (candidate last) once... publicly abused sen. richard shelby of alabama." (editorial, "there's something about (candidate last)," <em>the austin american-statesman</em>, 1/24/07)</p></span>



